WEBVTT

00:02.739 --> 00:04.743
♪ ♪

00:20.174 --> 00:22.277
[Gene] <i>The French toast
is exquisite today.</i>

00:22.278 --> 00:23.914
- Your father made it.
- You made it?

00:24.014 --> 00:25.984
It's so good
I assumed it was frozen.

00:25.985 --> 00:27.421
Uh, thank you?

00:27.555 --> 00:29.390
So, have you thought any more
about the contest, Dad?

00:29.391 --> 00:31.396
Ready to change your maybe
to a yes?

00:31.496 --> 00:33.066
Here's the flyer
for it again in case

00:33.166 --> 00:34.368
you need to refresh your memory.

00:34.468 --> 00:36.038
I'm familiar
with the flyer, Louise.

00:36.138 --> 00:38.777
You taped it to my face
after I fell asleep last night.

00:38.778 --> 00:41.448
- Yes.
- And I don't think you're
supposed to take things off

00:41.449 --> 00:43.318
the community center
bulletin board.

00:43.319 --> 00:44.722
How else do you expect me
to get a fun

00:44.723 --> 00:46.759
senior water aerobics poster?

00:46.760 --> 00:48.161
There are no good ones on eBay.

00:48.162 --> 00:49.765
Have you even read
the flyer, Dad?

00:49.766 --> 00:51.301
- Yeah.
- Read it again. Here we go.

00:51.302 --> 00:53.339
[moans]
"Come enter the Father-Daughter

00:53.340 --> 00:55.811
"Boogie Board Battle
for a fun day in the sun,

00:55.912 --> 00:58.449
hosted by Little Squirts
Surf Shirts."

00:58.450 --> 01:01.723
And it says first prize
is a hundred bucks.

01:01.724 --> 01:03.961
That's a lot of cheddar.
"Cheddar" means money, right?

01:04.061 --> 01:05.363
- On the streets?
- [Linda] Yeah, sure, Tina.

01:05.464 --> 01:07.100
Too bad it's only
for 12 and under.

01:07.101 --> 01:08.302
I'd get'er that cheddar.

01:08.303 --> 01:09.905
It also says everyone
who enters gets

01:09.906 --> 01:11.542
a free Little Squirts
Surf Shirt.

01:11.543 --> 01:14.013
Better be a new one, before
it gets any squirts on it.

01:14.014 --> 01:15.984
Uh, but we don't have
boogie boards, so--

01:15.985 --> 01:17.922
Well, the flyer says
they have loaners.

01:17.923 --> 01:20.260
- Oh.
- Come on. You, me, next weekend

01:20.361 --> 01:22.231
and a hundred smackers
that we split.

01:22.364 --> 01:24.502
Or you just give it all to me
because it's kind of weird

01:24.503 --> 01:26.405
- to split money with a child.
- Hmm.

01:26.506 --> 01:28.342
And didn't Mom say
you actually used to be good

01:28.343 --> 01:30.312
- at boogie boarding, somehow?
- He was.

01:30.313 --> 01:32.384
How? Was your body
different then?

01:32.484 --> 01:34.555
- Or was water different?
- Actually, your father's got

01:34.556 --> 01:37.360
- the perfect body
for boogie boarding.
- Thank you, Linda.

01:37.361 --> 01:38.931
He's very buoyant. Like a seal.

01:39.032 --> 01:41.101
How come we've never
seen you do it?

01:41.102 --> 01:42.337
[muffled grunting]

01:42.438 --> 01:44.241
Well, uh,
we opened the restaurant,

01:44.242 --> 01:47.013
and then, uh, we had kids,

01:47.014 --> 01:48.984
and I guess life happened.

01:49.084 --> 01:51.155
- But did it, though, for you?
- Louise...

01:51.156 --> 01:52.992
I mean, there was also
that other thing

01:52.993 --> 01:54.562
- that happened.
- [Gene] What thing?

01:54.563 --> 01:57.133
World War II? I'm not sure
how old you guys are.

01:57.134 --> 01:59.605
I think what your mom's
referring to is, one time,

01:59.606 --> 02:02.511
- I had a pretty vicious wipeout.
- He had a little incident--

02:02.512 --> 02:04.848
- Little incident?
I almost drowned.
- Drowned?

02:04.849 --> 02:06.252
You were in six inches of water.

02:06.352 --> 02:07.688
Yeah, deadly inches.

02:07.689 --> 02:09.993
I saw that, Lin.
You just shook your head.

02:10.094 --> 02:11.797
No, I didn't.
What's that over there?

02:11.931 --> 02:14.669
- [Tina] Hmm?
- Linda, I didn't even look
where you were pointing.

02:14.670 --> 02:15.739
I did. What did I miss?

02:15.839 --> 02:18.208
Honey, I believe
you believe it was scary.

02:18.209 --> 02:19.345
It was. It...

02:19.445 --> 02:21.015
Everyone, it was. You know what?

02:21.115 --> 02:23.185
- I-I'm not talking
about it anymore.
- Good.

02:23.186 --> 02:25.289
Well, what do you say,
ready to get back on the board?

02:25.290 --> 02:27.595
Win a hundred bucks?
And my love?

02:27.695 --> 02:28.763
- Um...
- Yeah?

02:28.764 --> 02:31.234
- All right, yes. Okay, fine.
- Ho, ho, yes.

02:31.235 --> 02:33.338
- Hmm.
- Good choice, good choice.

02:33.339 --> 02:35.043
It's the triumphant return
to the ocean

02:35.044 --> 02:37.814
for the voluptuous Seal-Man.

02:37.815 --> 02:39.587
[Teddy moans]
<i>I love eating.</i>

02:39.687 --> 02:41.689
- We know you do.
- Did I say that out loud?

02:41.690 --> 02:45.395
- Y-You did.
- So, your birthday's
this weekend.

02:45.396 --> 02:46.766
And remember
what you said last year.

02:46.767 --> 02:48.703
So what'd you end up doing
for your birthday, Teddy?

02:48.704 --> 02:51.109
- Well, I had that root canal,
and on my way home...
- Uh-huh.

02:51.209 --> 02:52.779
...I noticed my tires
were a little low...

02:52.879 --> 02:54.683
- Uh-huh.
- ...so I went
and filled them up.

02:54.783 --> 02:56.218
- Aw.
- Then I remembered
I was out of coffee filters

02:56.219 --> 02:57.722
- and toilet paper...
- [sighs]

02:57.723 --> 02:59.927
- ...so I swing by the store--
- Enough, enough!

03:00.027 --> 03:01.762
Teddy, I can't
take this anymore.

03:01.763 --> 03:03.800
Every year,
it gets sadder and sadder.

03:03.801 --> 03:07.239
I'm sorry, I'm-I'm just not
a big birthday person.

03:07.240 --> 03:08.443
Listen, you. Either next year

03:08.544 --> 03:10.146
you do something nice
for your birthday

03:10.147 --> 03:11.415
or I will make you.

03:11.416 --> 03:12.718
Are you threatening me, Linda?

03:12.819 --> 03:13.986
Promise me, Teddy.

03:13.987 --> 03:16.559
- Promise me.
- Okay, okay, I promise.

03:16.560 --> 03:19.031
So, what you doing this year?
It better be good.

03:19.132 --> 03:20.600
You gonna do something
with Kathleen?

03:20.601 --> 03:22.905
Eh, she's in Ireland
for a family reunion.

03:22.906 --> 03:23.741
Dang it.

03:23.875 --> 03:25.543
They're having it
in a town called Dingle.

03:25.544 --> 03:27.949
I said, "So you're gonna
be a bunch of Dingle-lings?"

03:27.950 --> 03:29.018
She didn't text me back.

03:29.118 --> 03:30.654
Okay, Teddy,
a promise is a promise.

03:30.655 --> 03:33.025
We're doing it here, birthday
party at the restaurant.

03:33.026 --> 03:35.429
We're gonna have cupcakes
and a candle

03:35.430 --> 03:37.199
and maybe we'll play
some party games.

03:37.200 --> 03:38.436
Lin, too much. Grown man.

03:38.537 --> 03:40.507
Okay, maybe just one round
of the limbo.

03:40.508 --> 03:42.511
- Lin...
- Fine, maybe no games.

03:42.512 --> 03:45.083
But yes, party. You hear me?

03:45.183 --> 03:47.121
Okay, okay.

03:47.221 --> 03:48.624
[phone ringing]

03:48.757 --> 03:50.960
- Bob's Burgers.
- We got to cancel
the birthday thing.

03:50.961 --> 03:52.666
- What?
- I'm going to a funeral.

03:52.766 --> 03:54.669
- What?
- Vernon, the guy
who owns the place

03:54.769 --> 03:57.240
that rents out jackhammers
and stuff to contractors?

03:57.241 --> 03:58.945
Ow! Just cut myself shaving.

03:59.045 --> 04:00.814
Anyway, he died. Heart attack.

04:00.815 --> 04:03.086
And the service
is today at Mort's.

04:03.186 --> 04:04.756
Oh, no. That's awful.

04:04.856 --> 04:06.893
- Yeah.
- Well, maybe we can do
your birthday

04:06.894 --> 04:08.563
- after the service?
- Eh...

04:08.564 --> 04:10.800
I-I won't be in the mood
to celebrate anything.

04:10.801 --> 04:13.072
I don't know why,
but funerals make me sad.

04:13.172 --> 04:15.209
Maybe it's 'cause my dad
died at a funeral.

04:15.210 --> 04:16.712
Next year, though. I-I promise.

04:16.713 --> 04:19.718
- But what if--
- Oh, boy. Sorry Linda,
I-I got to go.

04:19.719 --> 04:21.889
- Lot of blood here. Oh. [shouts]
- We could, we could do-- Ugh.

04:21.890 --> 04:23.459
Whoa. That's too much sunscreen.

04:23.460 --> 04:25.129
Uh, it-it feels like a lot.

04:25.130 --> 04:26.934
- Teddy's canceling his party.
- I heard.

04:27.034 --> 04:29.872
Uh, sorry you can't do the party
you were making him have.

04:29.873 --> 04:33.078
Aw, poop. I got the cupcakes
from Devondorf's.

04:33.079 --> 04:34.650
- Ooh.
- Well, we can still eat them.

04:34.750 --> 04:36.386
The cupcakes don't know
it's not our birthday.

04:36.486 --> 04:39.525
- Eh...
- Anyway, we have
a contest to win.

04:39.526 --> 04:40.794
- Bye.
- [Tina] Bye.

04:40.795 --> 04:42.731
Here's the first wave
for you to catch.

04:42.732 --> 04:44.301
Get it? [chuckles]

04:44.302 --> 04:46.672
I do. Thank you, Tina.

04:46.673 --> 04:48.577
You know, we probably should
have practiced a little,

04:48.677 --> 04:50.614
- boogie boarding.
- [laughs] Since when are we

04:50.615 --> 04:52.217
a "practice things" type
of family?

04:52.317 --> 04:54.421
Besides, if you were good
at boogie boarding,

04:54.422 --> 04:55.724
- how hard can it be?
- Well, that's--

04:55.725 --> 04:57.461
[Louise]
Look at driftwood.
It's doing it.

04:57.562 --> 04:58.831
Is it... did it practice that?

04:58.965 --> 05:00.568
[Bob]
Hmm, I mean,
it's not really the same.

05:00.668 --> 05:02.270
What, you think
you're better than driftwood?

05:02.271 --> 05:03.774
Most of it.

05:03.874 --> 05:05.411
- Sure there're a few pieces
that are--
- All right.

05:05.512 --> 05:07.883
Let's go pick out a board.
I can't with you.

05:08.016 --> 05:09.384
Look at these conditions.

05:09.385 --> 05:11.623
Beautiful, huge waves.

05:11.723 --> 05:13.392
Just in time for
the Little Squirts Surf Shirts

05:13.493 --> 05:15.598
Father-Daughter
Boogie Board Battle.

05:15.698 --> 05:17.935
Oh, geez.

05:19.238 --> 05:22.578
Come on, Dad.
Let's boogie, baby!

05:22.579 --> 05:23.981
Oh, boy.

05:27.956 --> 05:29.424
[Louise]
Okay, which one of you bad boys

05:29.425 --> 05:30.728
is gonna win me a hundred bucks?

05:30.828 --> 05:32.898
[high-pitched] Me, me.
[low-pitched] Me, me.

05:32.899 --> 05:34.836
[regular pitch]
Okay, everyone settle down.

05:34.937 --> 05:37.106
Hey, uh, I'm just gonna go talk
to the lifeguard real quick.

05:37.107 --> 05:39.611
Trash-talk him? Kind of weird
to do it to the lifeguard,

05:39.612 --> 05:42.283
but yeah, whatever pumps you up.
You want me to come?

05:42.284 --> 05:44.087
No, I... I-I got it.

05:44.088 --> 05:46.826
Uh, hi. How ya doing?
I was just wondering if--

05:46.827 --> 05:49.297
Is someone taking into account
how big these waves are?

05:49.298 --> 05:50.934
Yes. Don't worry.

05:50.935 --> 05:53.841
The ocean is perfectly safe
today for you and your child.

05:53.941 --> 05:55.544
Okay, but are you sure?

05:55.545 --> 05:57.380
I mean, you're seeing
those waves, right?

05:57.381 --> 05:59.018
Yes. I see the ocean.

05:59.118 --> 06:01.454
Notice how my big chair
is pointed right at it?

06:01.455 --> 06:04.362
- I see it at all times.
- But what about that wave?

06:04.462 --> 06:05.764
I mean, look-look at that one.

06:05.765 --> 06:08.336
Okay, not that one,
but, uh, there.

06:08.469 --> 06:09.839
- That one. Right?
- Yeah.

06:09.939 --> 06:12.278
Uh, okay, so, that one...
that one died down, too.

06:12.378 --> 06:13.580
- Mm-hmm.
- Uh, hold on, just--

06:13.581 --> 06:15.850
'Cause another big one is
coming any sec.

06:15.851 --> 06:17.152
I can't wait.

06:17.153 --> 06:19.959
Hey, Louise. I didn't know
you boogie-ed the boards.

06:20.059 --> 06:21.427
I'm gonna boogie this board.

06:21.428 --> 06:23.533
Did you bring a dad,
or are you gonna get a loaner?

06:23.534 --> 06:25.202
Uh, no. My dad's here.

06:25.203 --> 06:27.040
He's talking
to the announcer guy.

06:27.140 --> 06:29.211
- He's trying
to pitch him a jingle.
- Is that a euphemism?

06:29.212 --> 06:32.349
<i>♪ Dum-dum-dum, who's the shirt
that's full of squirts? ♪</i>

06:32.350 --> 06:36.627
<i>♪ Da-da-da, da, makes all
the jellyfish go berserk. ♪</i>

06:36.760 --> 06:39.265
- Oh, hi, Mr. B.
- Oh, hi, Courtney.

06:39.365 --> 06:41.435
- Break a leg out there.
- Wha-What?

06:41.436 --> 06:43.038
It's just an expression.

06:43.039 --> 06:45.075
- God. [laughs]
- Oh. Right.

06:45.076 --> 06:47.781
Uh, seems like we have a little
time before the contest starts.

06:47.782 --> 06:50.755
Should we jump in so I can
master this sport real quick?

06:50.855 --> 06:52.024
Yup. Yup.

06:52.124 --> 06:54.529
Dah. Poor, dumb, old,
dead equipment rental guy

06:54.629 --> 06:56.131
and his lousy timing.

06:56.132 --> 06:59.505
Sorry, but-- Ugh. Teddy's never
gonna celebrate his birthday.

06:59.506 --> 07:01.242
- Hey, there's always
next year, right?
- Yeah.

07:01.342 --> 07:03.613
Teddy's friends aren't <i>always</i>
gonna die on his birthday.

07:03.614 --> 07:05.784
And if they do,
we should probably move.

07:05.785 --> 07:08.623
So, is anyone else thinking
it's weird

07:08.624 --> 07:10.493
that we haven't
eaten those cupcakes yet?

07:10.494 --> 07:11.896
- Ease into it, Gene.
- Too soon.

07:11.897 --> 07:13.900
It's what
Teddy would have wanted.

07:13.901 --> 07:16.572
So, yeah. Wait for the wave
to pick up the back of the board

07:16.573 --> 07:18.342
and then kick like crazy.

07:18.343 --> 07:20.446
Uh, here's one.

07:21.115 --> 07:22.519
- Fun, right?
- Yeah.

07:22.619 --> 07:25.925
If you like very slow rides
that only go six feet.

07:26.025 --> 07:27.561
Oh, well, uh, yeah.

07:27.562 --> 07:29.698
Dad, everyone is out there.

07:29.699 --> 07:32.537
- Why are we here?
- Uh, you know the old saying.

07:32.538 --> 07:34.775
"Water white? Doing all right.

07:34.776 --> 07:37.881
Water... curl?
Uh, get out of there, girl."

07:37.882 --> 07:40.353
- No, I've never heard that.
- Well, it's an old saying.

07:40.453 --> 07:42.758
- And you're young.
- Really? Who said it?

07:42.759 --> 07:44.695
Uh, Mark Twain. You know him?

07:44.696 --> 07:46.431
- Never heard of him.
- He's a famous writer.

07:46.432 --> 07:47.634
About surfing?

07:47.635 --> 07:49.470
Some of it, yeah.
On the Mississippi.

07:49.471 --> 07:52.042
But those waves are bigger.
I'm no oceanologist,

07:52.043 --> 07:55.851
but wouldn't big waves make you
go farther and win the contest?

07:55.951 --> 07:58.322
Uh, well, I mean,
some people might say that.

07:58.422 --> 07:59.925
But others would say,

07:59.926 --> 08:02.464
"Wave too big,
don't dance that jig."

08:02.565 --> 08:06.104
- Mark Twain again?
- No, that's, uh... Jamiroquai.

08:06.205 --> 08:09.478
Dad, where's the golden-boy
boogie-boarder from yesteryear?

08:09.612 --> 08:11.616
'Cause I'd love to meet him.

08:13.620 --> 08:14.755
[gasping loudly]

08:14.756 --> 08:16.191
[Louise]
Come on, Dad!

08:16.192 --> 08:18.096
Boogie your butt on out here!

08:18.196 --> 08:19.398
Oh, boy.

08:19.498 --> 08:21.635
[Gene]
<i>Mom, the birthday party is gone.</i>

08:21.636 --> 08:25.475
But the cupcakes are here,
alive and well, and so are we.

08:25.476 --> 08:27.447
Gene's right. It's time
to kill those cupcakes.

08:27.448 --> 08:28.850
With-with our mouths.

08:28.851 --> 08:30.486
All right. Fine.

08:30.487 --> 08:31.656
Yay!

08:31.657 --> 08:32.991
[entry bells jingling]

08:32.992 --> 08:35.029
- Oh, uh, hold off
on the cupcakes.
- Damn it!

08:35.030 --> 08:37.567
Oh, hey, Teddy.
You're here... with some people.

08:37.568 --> 08:39.771
Yeah. Handymen and handywoman.

08:39.772 --> 08:41.175
I'm Joyce, the handyma'am.

08:41.275 --> 08:44.447
Ha. I love it.
Aw, but sorry about your friend.

08:44.448 --> 08:47.052
Linda, you remember Glenn,
and this is Lou.

08:47.053 --> 08:48.756
- Hi, Lou.
- Hello.

08:48.757 --> 08:50.259
So, did Teddy tell you
it's his bir--

08:50.360 --> 08:52.598
Uh, we're just here to have
a beer and talk about Vernon.

08:52.599 --> 08:54.168
- That's all.
- Okay. Okay.

08:54.301 --> 08:56.471
[sniffles] I didn't think
I was gonna get so broken up.

08:56.472 --> 08:58.743
Yeah, you cried loudly
at the service.

08:58.744 --> 09:00.747
- Super loud.
- Aw.

09:00.748 --> 09:02.552
Hey, this round's on the house.

09:02.652 --> 09:03.987
Some beer for your tears.

09:04.088 --> 09:06.158
And... maybe some fries
for your cries?

09:06.258 --> 09:07.963
Oh, okay. Yeah, sounds good.

09:08.063 --> 09:10.232
- Lots of fries.
- Kids, uh, give me a hand.

09:10.233 --> 09:11.535
[whispering]
Secret meeting.

09:11.536 --> 09:13.139
[whispering]
Mom forgot how to use the fryer.

09:13.239 --> 09:14.676
[whispering]
So embarrassing.

09:14.776 --> 09:16.912
Listen,
I think we can work with this.

09:16.913 --> 09:18.282
Teddy and his friends will talk
about Vernon,

09:18.283 --> 09:19.986
they'll get sick of that,
and then they'll be ready

09:20.086 --> 09:21.589
to move on
to something a little more fun.

09:21.590 --> 09:23.158
Are you sure that's what they--

09:23.159 --> 09:25.163
Tina, you are this close to
not being invited to the party.

09:25.263 --> 09:26.567
- Got it. Got it.
- Aah!

09:26.700 --> 09:28.537
- Not yet.
- But soon.

09:28.671 --> 09:29.971
Louise, are you sure

09:29.972 --> 09:32.010
you don't want to go back
to where we were?

09:32.110 --> 09:33.914
Loserville? No.

09:34.014 --> 09:35.918
Ooh, look at this one!
Let's catch it.

09:36.018 --> 09:37.588
No, that--
It looks pretty big.

09:37.688 --> 09:38.756
- Let's duck under it.
- Ugh.

09:38.757 --> 09:40.761
- [panting]
- Ah, come on.

09:40.762 --> 09:42.263
We should have taken it!

09:42.363 --> 09:44.200
No, that-that wave was, um,

09:44.201 --> 09:45.604
- gross.
- Gross?

09:45.605 --> 09:47.107
Yeah. Squishy and gross.

09:47.207 --> 09:49.812
Those are technical terms.
Uh, you'll learn it all later.

09:49.813 --> 09:52.450
Oh, ho, ho,
here comes another good one!

09:52.451 --> 09:53.953
- Louise, I don't think--
- I'm going for it!

09:53.954 --> 09:56.257
- No, no, no. No!
- Yes, yes, yes.

09:56.258 --> 09:58.095
[whooping]

09:58.196 --> 09:59.497
That was amazing.

09:59.498 --> 10:01.502
Dad, did you see me?!

10:01.503 --> 10:04.542
Yeah. G-Good, uh, job with it.

10:04.543 --> 10:05.878
Why didn't you tell me

10:05.978 --> 10:07.582
that oceans are like
free roller coasters,

10:07.715 --> 10:10.019
and not just big, stinky,
wet places where fish pee?

10:10.020 --> 10:12.657
Oh, you know,
Louise, they also poop.

10:12.658 --> 10:14.428
There's less poop
closer to shore.

10:14.563 --> 10:16.332
It's the-the jet stream,
I think, so--

10:16.432 --> 10:18.169
Okay,
why are you being so weird?

